The paper deals with the performance of MIMO broadcast and interference channels in the presence of imperfect and delayed feedback. This topic falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of channel state information (CSI) on the performance, which is related to the signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper derives the degrees of freedom (DoF) region, which is a measure of the capacity of the channel, and this falls under the computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) sub-category.
